From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude.ai.2026@simonlaux.de>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 02:25:41 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 50/64] web-app: composer completion menu (:emoji: now,
 mentions later)

A scrollable, keyboard-navigable menu that pops up over the composer and
completes what you're typing. First consumer is :colon-emoji: completion;
built as a generic primitive so a future @mention menu is just another
provider.

- completion/findActiveToken.ts: pure caret token detector with a
  start/whitespace boundary guard, so it never fires inside http:// or 12:30.
- completion/emojiProvider.ts: reuses the already-bundled @emoji-mart/data
  (no new dependency), ranking exact/prefix shortcodes first and matching
  keywords; inserts the Unicode glyph.
- completion/CompletionMenu.tsx: generic presentational list (active-row
  highlight, scroll-into-view, click/hover), emoji-agnostic.
- ComposerMessageInput.tsx: detects the token on change/caret-move, drives
  arrow-nav (wrap) + Enter-select + Escape-dismiss, and replaces the :token
  with the emoji via the existing caret-restore path. While the menu is open
  it owns Arrow/Enter/Escape, so Enter=send and ArrowUp=edit-last don't fire.
- Menu floats above the composer, anchored to .lower-bar (now position:
  relative); the emoji/app pickers are siblings and unaffected.
- tests/completion.test.ts: mocha/chai check for the token detector + provider.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
